1.2: A stub binder is an object that helps define the stub by binding method name to the stub method.
A stub binder is an object that helps define the stub by binding method name to the stub method.

Defines the function to be called for the method name and arguments bound to this StubBinder.

If then or thenReturn has been previously called on this StubBinder then the given stub func will be called only after the stubs passed previously have been called. Afterwards, if no other calls are made to then or thenReturn for this StubBinder then the given func will be used for every further invocation. See #when for complete examples. Defines the constant return value for the stub represented by this StubBinder.
